Thread-SigMask

This module provides per-thread signal masks. On non-threaded perl's, it will be effectively the same as POSIX::sigprocmask. The interface works exactly the same as sigprocmask.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Thread::SigMask

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Thread-SigMask

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Thread-SigMask

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Thread-SigMask

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Thread-SigMask/


